---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import { CONSULTING } from "@consts";
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { createConsultingServiceSchema } from "@lib/schemas";

const consultingSchema = createConsultingServiceSchema(Astro.site!);
---

<PageLayout title={CONSULTING.TITLE} description={CONSULTING.DESCRIPTION}>
  <script
    is:inline
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify(consultingSchema)}
  />

  <Container>
    <h1 class="animate text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
      Staff-Level Engineering Consulting & Mentoring
    </h1>
    <div class="space-y-16">
      <section>
        <article class="space-y-4">
          <p class="animate">
            Is your engineering environment feeling "small or slow"? Are your
            tools, pipelines, and architecture struggling to keep up with your
            team's growth?
          </p>

          <p class="animate">
            I help engineering organizations scale their platforms, people, and
            processes. As a Staff Engineer who has scaled systems for hundreds
            of developers at <a
              href="https://www.leboncoin.fr"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>leboncoin.fr</strong></a
            > and <a
              href="https://www.kleinanzeigen.de"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Kleinanzeigen</strong></a
            >, I solve the complex bottlenecks in <strong
              >platform engineering</strong
            >, <strong>developer experience (DevEx)</strong>, and <strong
              >systems architecture</strong
            >.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="animate space-y-6">
        <h2 class="animate text-lg font-semibold">My Services</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <h3 class="animate font-semibold">
              1. Platform & DevEx Acceleration
            </h3>
            <ul class="animate space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>What it is:</strong> A top-to-bottom audit and rebuild of
                your development and deployment pipeline. We find what's "slow" and
                make it fast.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>What you deliver:</strong> A pragmatic, actionable roadmap
                to fix your CI/CD, testing, and infrastructure bottlenecks. I'll
                apply the same principles I used at <a
                  href="https://www.leboncoin.fr"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>leboncoin.fr</strong></a
                > to:
                <ul class="animate mt-2 ml-4 space-y-1">
                  <li>
                    <strong>Migrate your entire CI/CD</strong> from legacy systems
                    (like Travis) to modern platforms (like GitHub Actions).
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Crush CI times</strong> from 1-2 hours down to <strong
                      >under 10 minutes</strong
                    >.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Optimize infrastructure</strong>, in one case
                    reducing production pods from ~500 to ~150.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Teams held back by slow builds, flaky
                tests, and a high Mean Lead Time for Changes (MLTC).
              </li>
              <li>
                “Read the case study: <a
                  href="/blog/06-taming-the-ci-beast-part-4"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  ><strong>How I reduced CI times from 50m to 9m.” </strong></a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-3">
            <h3 class="animate font-semibold">
              2. Modern Architecture & Migration Strategy
            </h3>
            <ul class="animate space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>What it is:</strong> A strategic plan to scale your architecture
                and your engineering organization together.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>What you deliver:</strong> A clear path forward, whether
                it's designing a <strong>scalable monorepo</strong> or <strong
                  >migrating a legacy monolith</strong
                >. I'm currently leading this at <a
                  href="https://www.kleinanzeigen.de"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Kleinanzeigen</strong></a
                >, migrating a jQuery/Java SpringBoot system to a <strong
                  >Node.js, Astro, and React</strong
                > stack, resulting in a <strong
                  >5x improvement in development speed</strong
                > for the teams involved.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Organizations struggling with a monolith,
                scaling to 100+ engineers, or needing to design a high-performing
                monorepo for shared packages and micro-frontends.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-3">
            <h3 class="animate font-semibold">
              3. Staff+ & Neurodiversity Mentorship
            </h3>
            <ul class="animate space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong>What it is:</strong> A 1-on-1 mentorship program for engineers
                and leaders. This program has two tracks:
                <ol class="animate mt-2 ml-4 space-y-1">
                  <li>
                    <strong>Technical Leadership:</strong> A structured growth plan
                    for Senior engineers on the path to Staff/Principal. We focus
                    on technical strategy, architectural vision, and cross-team influence.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Navigating the Workplace:</strong> Dedicated, empathetic
                    coaching for <strong
                      >neurodivergent (ND) professionals</strong
                    >. If you are struggling with your work environment and
                    would like the perspective of someone who has navigated it,
                    I am here to help.
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Ambitious engineers, new Staff-level leaders,
                and any neurodivergent professional in tech seeking confidential
                guidance.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="animate space-y-6">
        <h2 class="animate text-lg font-semibold">Who This Is For</h2>
        <p class="animate">I provide the most value to...</p>
        <ul class="animate space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>CTOs or VPs of Engineering</strong> at scaling companies whose
            teams are "feeling slow" and blocked by their platform.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Engineering Managers or Directors</strong> who need a concrete
            plan for a complex, large-scale migration (e.g., monolith to micro-frontends).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Senior Engineers</strong> on the path to Staff who need a mentor
            to guide them.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Neurodivergent Professionals</strong> in tech who would like
            coaching from someone with shared experience.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="animate space-y-6">
        <h2 class="animate text-lg font-semibold">
          My Consulting Philosophy: Pragmatism over Dogma
        </h2>
        <article class="space-y-4">
          <p class="animate">
            My approach is built on one core idea: <strong
              >"Change is Requirement #0."</strong
            >
          </p>
          <p class="animate">
            I don't believe in "best practices" that don't fit your context. As
            a self-taught engineer from a humanities background, I see code as
            prose and architecture as a story.
          </p>
          <p class="animate">
            My job isn't to force my opinions. It's to act as a <strong
              >teacher and a problem-solver</strong
            >. I'll become a historian of your system, understand <em>why</em> it
            was built, and give your team the context, real-world experience, and
            confidence to make the best decision for your specific case.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="animate space-y-6">
        <h2 class="animate text-lg font-semibold">Let's Talk</h2>
        <article class="space-y-4">
          <p class="animate">
            Ready to scale your team's platform and speed? Send me an email at <a
              href={`mailto:consulting@danilovelasquez.com?subject=Consulting%20Inquiry&body=Hi%20Danilo,%20I%20read%20your%20consulting%20page%20and%20would%20like%20to%20discuss...`}
              ><strong>consulting@danilovelasquez.com</strong></a
            > with a brief description of your challenges.
          </p>
          <p class="animate">
            We can then schedule a <a
              href="https://cal.com/danilovelasquez/30min"
              target="_blank"><strong>free, 30-minute discovery call</strong></a
            > to see if we're a good fit.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </div>
  </Container>
</PageLayout>
